			<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
			<p class="lead">
				Plain-language terms for using <code>api.flipagent.dev</code>, the dashboard, and our open-source packages. Last updated {updated}.
			</p>

			<h2>What flipagent provides</h2>
			<p>An HTTP API at <code>api.flipagent.dev</code> covering the online reselling cycle — search, evaluation, buying, listing, fulfillment, finance — plus an MCP server for AI-agent integrations and open-source TypeScript packages (the SDK <code>@flipagent/sdk</code>, MCP server <code>flipagent-mcp</code>, CLI installer <code>flipagent-cli</code>). The hosted service caches eBay public listing data, proxies eBay OAuth on your behalf, runs server-side margin-scoring math, and meters per-call usage by tier.</p>

			<h2>Your account</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>You're responsible for keeping API keys + your eBay account credentials secure. Revoke at the dashboard immediately if you suspect a leak.</li>
				<li>One account per person or organization. Don't share keys across multiple businesses on the same plan.</li>
				<li>You must be 18 or older and able to enter into binding agreements. The service is not directed at children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect data from them.</li>
				<li>You represent that you, your organization, and your end users are not on a U.S. or other applicable sanctions list (OFAC SDN, EU consolidated, UK HMT) and that you will not use the service in a sanctioned jurisdiction.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Acceptable use</h2>
			<p>The detailed operational rules — listing content, account hygiene, buy-side automation, volume, redistribution — live in the <a href="/legal/aup/">Acceptable Use Policy</a>, which is incorporated into these terms by reference. A material AUP violation is a material breach of these terms. The headline rules:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Stay within your tier's monthly allowance; we throttle.</li>
				<li>Don't redistribute raw eBay listing content (titles, descriptions, photos, seller details) divorced from the original <code>ebay.com/itm/...</code> URL.</li>
				<li>Don't build derivative datasets for resale outside the eBay context.</li>
				<li>Don't ingest eBay REST API responses (returned via flipagent's <code>transport=rest</code> path) into any generative AI model for training, fine-tuning, embedding, or retrieval-augmented generation. eBay's Developer Program License Agreement reserves this right; we pass the obligation through. The scrape transport is not subject to this restriction.</li>
				<li>Buy-side actions (<code>/v1/purchases</code>) must include human review of each order before placement, unless your eBay developer account holds Order API approval. eBay's User Agreement (effective Feb 20, 2026) prohibits "buy-for-me agents, LLM-driven bots, or any end-to-end flow that attempts to place orders without human review."</li>
				<li>Don't list items that violate eBay's Verified Rights Owner (VeRO) program, prohibited-and-restricted-items policy, or any equivalent intellectual-property or marketplace-integrity rule.</li>
				<li>Don't operate an eBay account that is currently suspended or under an open enforcement action whose terms would be violated by automated activity.</li>
				<li>Don't resell raw access to <code>api.flipagent.dev</code> as your own service.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Tier limits + billing</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Tier allowances reset monthly (UTC calendar month) and are counted by metered API call against the marketplace and intelligence endpoints under <code>/v1/*</code> (items, categories, products, evaluate, ship). Management routes (<code>/v1/me/*</code>, <code>/v1/connect/*</code>, <code>/v1/billing/*</code>, <code>/v1/takedown</code>, <code>/v1/health</code>) are free. The free tier provides a one-time, lifetime credit allowance, not a monthly reset.</li>
				<li>Stripe handles payment. Subscription changes take effect immediately for upgrades and at the end of the billing period for downgrades. Subscriptions auto-renew at the cadence selected at checkout until cancelled; you can cancel at any time from the dashboard or the Stripe customer portal.</li>
				<li>Refunds: pro-rated on cancellation only when the cause is a service-side outage or material breach of these terms. Email <a href="mailto:hello@flipagent.dev">hello@flipagent.dev</a>.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Open-source packages</h2>
			<p>The MIT-licensed packages (<code>@flipagent/sdk</code>, <code>flipagent-mcp</code>, <code>flipagent-cli</code>, <code>@flipagent/ebay-scraper</code>, <code>@flipagent/types/ebay</code>, <code>@flipagent/types</code>) and the FSL-licensed <code>@flipagent/api</code> backend source are governed by their own LICENSE files, not these terms. You can use them with or without an account here. The warranty disclaimer below applies only to the hosted service; the OSS packages are distributed without warranty under their own license terms.</p>

			<h2>Connected eBay account</h2>
			<p>When you connect an eBay account at <code>/v1/connect/ebay</code>, you authorize flipagent to act on your sell-side resources (listings, sales, payouts, transactions, policies) and — when REST transport is approved — your purchases, using the OAuth refresh token you grant. Refresh tokens are valid for up to 18 months under eBay's standard issuance. Disconnecting at flipagent removes the token from our database; to revoke flipagent's access at eBay's end, also visit eBay's "Account → Permissions" page.</p>
			<p><strong>Your eBay account is your responsibility.</strong> You represent that the eBay account you connect is yours (or one you are authorized to operate), in good standing, and not subject to a suspension, MC011 restriction, selling-limit appeal, or other open enforcement action that would be violated by automated activity. You agree that any action flipagent takes against eBay under your OAuth grant — listing, buying, messaging, refunding, fulfilling — counts as your action under eBay's User Agreement, and that you are solely responsible for compliance with eBay's terms, policies, and seller protections in connection with that activity.</p>
			<p><strong>Bridge transport — your own browser, your own session.</strong> When you install the flipagent Chrome extension and use bridge transport, jobs execute inside your already-logged-in eBay tab using your own cookies and session. flipagent does not store your eBay password and never logs into eBay on your behalf. The bridge is a remote-control surface for software you are running locally; the activity it performs is your activity for purposes of eBay's User Agreement and any applicable law.</p>
			<p><strong>Account actions by eBay are not flipagent's liability.</strong> eBay may, at its sole discretion, restrict, suspend, or close accounts that engage in automated activity, exceed selling limits, list against VeRO, or otherwise violate its policies — whether or not the activity originated from flipagent. To the maximum extent permitted by law, flipagent is not liable for lost sales, lost listings, withheld payouts, or any other harm caused by an eBay-side enforcement action against your account.</p>

			<h2>Service availability</h2>
			<p>We aim for 99.5% monthly uptime on the hosted API. We don't currently offer a contractual SLA. The service depends on third-party marketplaces (today eBay; later others) whose APIs, web surfaces, anti-automation measures, and user agreements may change without notice. flipagent makes no warranty that the service will continue to function with any third-party marketplace, and we may modify, suspend, or discontinue any feature at any time to remain compliant with upstream terms.</p>

