			<h2>Governing law + venue</h2>
			<p>These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, USA, without regard to conflict-of-laws rules. For Disputes carved out of arbitration above, the state and federal courts located in Wilmington, Delaware have exclusive jurisdiction; you and flipagent each waive any objection to that venue and any right to a jury trial. Any claim must be brought within one (1) year after it accrues, or it is permanently barred, except where a longer period is required by mandatory local law.</p>

			<h2>DMCA + IP notices</h2>
			<p>flipagent is not registered with the U.S. Copyright Office's DMCA designated-agent directory under 17 U.S.C. §512(c)(2). The bulk of our infrastructure is a cache + scraper rather than a UGC host, so the §512(c) safe harbor does not naturally apply to our model. We do operate a private takedown channel that accepts notices in the §512(c)(3) shape so rights holders have a clean path that does not require a lawsuit; submit at <a href="/legal/takedown/">/legal/takedown</a> or email <a href="mailto:legal@flipagent.dev">legal@flipagent.dev</a>. If your content was removed in response to a takedown that you believe is mistaken or wrongful, email <a href="mailto:legal@flipagent.dev">legal@flipagent.dev</a> with a counter-notice in the §512(g) shape; approved counter-notices restore the content. See <a href="/legal/compliance/">/legal/compliance</a> for the full operational picture.</p>

			<h2>Termination</h2>
			<p>You can close your account anytime by emailing <a href="mailto:hello@flipagent.dev">hello@flipagent.dev</a> or, when available, via the dashboard's account-deletion path. We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms or the AUP; we'll explain why and give you a chance to rectify unless the breach is severe (abuse, fraud, IP infringement, court order, or upstream-marketplace enforcement requiring immediate action). Sections that by their nature should survive termination — Acceptable Use, Indemnification, Disclaimer, Limitation of Liability, Dispute Resolution, Governing Law, DMCA, and General — survive.</p>

			<h2>Changes</h2>
			<p>If we change these terms materially, we'll send a heads-up to your account email at least 30 days before the change takes effect, except where a shorter period is required by upstream-marketplace amendments (in which case we'll match the shortest period eBay or another upstream gives us). Continuing to use the service after the effective date means you accept the new terms; if you don't, close your account before the effective date.</p>

